e"},"da":{"about 16 October 1286–before 7 March 1355":"omkring 16. oktober 1286–før 7. marts 1355","1286–1355":"1286–1355","–1265":"–1265","1279–1355":"1279–1355","1315–1362":"1315–1362","1256–1295":"1256–1295","1270–1295":"1270–1295","6 October 1298":"6. oktober 1298","1286":"1286","1362":"1362","1295":"1295","1270":"1270","1315":"1315","about 16 October 1286":"omkring 16. oktober 1286","18 October 1295":"18. oktober 1295","1279":"1279","1256":"1256","1355":"1355","1265":"1265","before 7 March 1355":"før 7. marts 1355","8 November 1295":"8. november 1295","Ireland":"Irland","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"nl":{"about 16 October 1286–before 7 March 1355":"circa 16 oktober 1286–vóór 7 maart 1355","1286–1355":"1286–1355","–1265":"–1265","1279–1355":"1279–1355","1315–1362":"1315–1362","1256–1295":"1256–1295","1270–1295":"1270–1295","6 October 1298":"6 oktober 1298","1286":"1286","1362":"1362","1295":"1295","1270":"1270","1315":"1315","about 16 October 1286":"circa 16 oktober 1286","18 October 1295":"18 oktober 1295","1279":"1279","1256":"1256","1355":"1355","1265":"1265","before 7 March 1355":"vóór 7 maart 1355","8 November 1295":"8 november 1295","Ireland":"Ierland","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"England"},"en":{"about 16 October 1286–before 7 March 1355":"about 16 October 1286–before 7 March 1355","1286–1355":"1286–1355","–1265":"–1265","1279–1355":"1279–1355","1315–1362":"1315–1362","1256–1295":"1256–1295","1270–1295":"1270–1295","6 October 1298":"6 October 1298","1286":"1286","1362":"1362","1295":"1295","1270":"1270","1315":"1315","about 16 October 1286":"about 16 October 1286","18 October 1295":"18 October 1295","1279":"1279","1256":"1256","1355":"1355","1265":"1265","before 7 March 1355":"before 7 March 1355","8 November 1295":"8 November 1295","Ireland":"Ireland","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Rockley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name chiefly from Rockley in Worsbrough (WR Yorks). There is also evidence for surnames deriving from Rockley (Wilts), Ruckley (Shrops), Rockley in High Bray (Devon), and perhaps Rookley (IoW)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Maud","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Medieval vernacular form of   Matilda .  This form was characteristically Low German (i.e. including medieval Dutch and Flemish). The wife of  William the Conqueror , who bore this name, was the daughter of  Baldwin , Count of Flanders. In Flemish and Dutch the letter <i>-t-</i> was generally lost when it occurred between vowels, giving forms such as <i>Ma(h)auld</i>. <i>Maud</i> or <i>Matilda</i> was also the name of the daughter (  1102–67 ) of  Henry I  of England; she was married early in life to the Holy Roman Emperor  Henry V , and later disputed the throne of England with her cousin  Stephen . In  1128  she married  Geoffrey , Count of Anjou. A medieval chronicler commented, ‘she was a good woman, but she had little bliss with him’. The name <i>Maud</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Maud Rockley was born about 16 October 1286, in Ireland, her father, Philip De Rockele, was 30 and her mother, Joan Of Essex, was 17. She married Sir Maurice Bruyn on 6 October 1298, in Hampshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died before 7 March 1355."},"et":{"about 16 October 1286–before 7 March 1355":"umbes 16. oktoober 1286–enne 7. märtsi 1355","1286–1355":"1286–1355","–1265":"–1265","1279–1355":"1279–1355","1315–1362":"1315–1